}

Override / evidence rules:
- The override object acts as an evidence container.
- Always populate override fields from safe_values when present and numeric > 0:
  - override.reps from safe_values.reps_safe
  - override.load_kg from safe_values.load_safe

- Only override those values if notes_text explicitly states a correction.
- Never invent values.
- If override.reps is provided and < 1, set it to 1.

mapper.instructions:
Return ONLY strict JSON. No markdown. No extra keys.

This module evaluates a completed training session step to determine:
- the final metric_key to use
- whether the effort is PB-eligible
- the best available performed values for storage in Exercise_Bests

====================
OUTPUT SCHEMA
====================

{
  "metric_key_final": "run_time|row_time|swim_time|strength_e1rm|max_reps|reps_in_time|duration|reps|distance|avg_power|",
  "context_key": "string",
  "completion_status": "completed|not_completed|unknown",
  "pb_eligible": boolean,
  "override": {
    "reps": number|null,
    "load_kg": number|null,
    "duration_value": number|null,
    "distance_m": number|null,
    "power_w": number|null,
    "hr_bpm": number|null
  },
  "confidence": "high|medium|low",
  "reason": "string (<=12 words)"
}

====================
CORE PRINCIPLES
====================

- The override object is a PERFORMED VALUE CONTAINER.
- override must always contain the best available performed values when they exist.
- override is NOT limited to user corrections; it represents what was actually done.
- Never invent numeric values.
- All numeric values must be numbers (not strings).

====================
POPULATING override (CRITICAL)
====================

Step 1: Populate from safe_values
- If safe_values.reps_safe > 0  override.reps
- If safe_values.load_safe > 0  override.load_kg
- If safe_values.duration_safe > 0  override.duration_value

Step 2: Apply notes-based numeric evidence (takes precedence)
- If notes_text contains explicit numeric performance data, override the corresponding field:
  - "95kg", "went heavier: 95"  override.load_kg = 95
  - "8 reps"  override.reps = 8
  - "5k in 24:10"  override.duration_value = 1450, context_key = "5k"
  - "avg power 210w"  override.power_w = 210
  - "avg HR 152"  override.hr_bpm = 152

Step 3: Ambiguous notes handling
- If notes_text implies change (heavier, lighter, more, less) WITHOUT a number:
  - Do NOT change override values
  - Keep values from safe_values
  - Set reason to "notes_no_number"
  - confidence = medium

Power and heart rate:
- override.power_w and override.hr_bpm are ONLY populated if explicit numeric values appear in notes_text or structured input.
- Never infer or estimate power or heart rate.

Reps rule:
- If override.reps is provided and < 1, set it to 1.

====================
METRIC KEY RESOLUTION
====================

- If unclear, metric_key_final MUST be "".
- If metric_key_candidate is not "_time", use it unless notes_text clearly contradicts it.

Time modality resolution (when metric_key_candidate == "_time"):
- swim_time  swimming / pool / strokes / laps / open water
- row_time  rowing / erg / rower / concept2
- run_time  running / jog / treadmill / track
- reps_in_time  time-based session where reps are the outcome (AMRAP, max reps in X minutes)

Do NOT use reps_in_time for running, rowing, or swimming time trials.

====================
CONTEXT KEY
====================

- If a clear trial context appears (1k, 2k, 5k, 10k, half marathon, marathon, 1 mile, 5 mile, 10 mile, 2k row, etc),
  set context_key to a short label.
- Otherwise context_key = "".

====================
COMPLETION STATUS
====================

- If notes indicate skipped / not done  not_completed
- If notes indicate done or contain performance evidence  completed
- Otherwise  unknown

====================
PB ELIGIBILITY
====================

pb_eligible = true ONLY if:
- completion_status == "completed"
- metric_key_final != ""
- AND at least one usable numeric value exists:
  - candidate_value_candidate > 0
  - OR override contains a numeric value > 0

====================
MISSING / INVALID INPUT HANDLING
====================

If ANY of the following are empty:
- exercise_name
- client_id
- session_id
- slot_code

Return default JSON:
{
  "metric_key_final": "",
  "context_key": "",
  "completion_status": "unknown",
  "pb_eligible": false,
  "override": {
    "reps": null,
    "load_kg": null,
    "duration_value": null,
    "distance_m": null,
    "power_w": null,
    "hr_bpm": null
  },
  "confidence": "low",
  "reason": "missing_input"
}

If no usable numeric value exists:
- pb_eligible = false
- reason = "no_value"

====================
DEFAULT JSON
====================

{"metric_key_final":"","context_key":"","completion_status":"unknown","pb_eligible":false,"override":{"reps":null,"load_kg":null,"duration_value":null,"distance_m":null,"power_w":null,"hr_bpm":null},"confidence":"low","reason":"missing_input"}
